cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.SY, cs.DC

This paper discusses the effectiveness of code randomization in mitigating code reuse attacks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves measuring the impact of code randomization on the Turing completeness of JIT-ROP payloads, which relates to programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper involves measuring the availability and quality of gadgets, which relates to system design and analysis (cs.SY) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
